@node ptable_library__unified_partition_table_library "ptable.library: unified partition-table library"
@{b}@{u}ptable.library: unified partition-table library@{uu}@{ub}

@{fg shine}ptable.library@{fg text} is the AmigaOS partition-table library. It parses every
partition scheme a removable card might carry ( @{b}RDB@{ub} , @{b}MBR@{ub} , @{b}GPT@{ub} , and
the partition-table-less @{b}flat@{ub} superfloppy, a whole-disk FAT volume) and
publishes the result into @{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} . A device driver and a
filesystem handler then share that one parse instead of each carrying
its own.

You do not run @{fg shine}ptable.library@{fg text} ; other components open it. This document
explains what it does and how its behaviour is configured. The @{fg shine}lsptres@{fg text}
tool (see @{"  __PAIRED_2__  " link "lsptres.guide/Main"} ) shows what it has discovered at runtime. The library ships
alongside its consumer @{fg shine}compactflash.device@{fg text} , or embedded in a Kickstart
ROM for cold-boot autoboot (see the amigaos-kickstart-builder
(https://github.com/pulchart/amigaos-kickstart-builder) repo).

----------------------------------------
@{"<< Prev" link Main}  @{"Contents" link Main}  @{"Next >>" link What_it_does}

@endnode

@node What_it_does "What it does"
@{b}What it does@{ub}

@{fg shine}ptable.library@{fg text} has two jobs, used at two different times.

  * @{b}Cold-boot RDB autoboot.@{ub} At Kickstart cold start, before DOS exists, the
    @{fg shine}compactflash.dosboot@{fg text} module calls @{fg shine}BootScanPartitions@{fg text} . The library walks the
    RDB on the card, loads any filesystem handlers stored in the RDB into
    @{fg shine}FileSystem.resource@{fg text} , and registers each partition: bootable ones via
    @{fg shine}AddBootNode@{fg text} (they appear in the Early Startup boot menu), mountable-only ones
    via @{fg shine}AddDosNode@{fg text} . This is what lets you boot directly from an RDB-partitioned
    card in the PCMCIA slot.

  * @{b}DOS-time scan and automount.@{ub} When a card is hotplugged after the machine is
    up, the consumer calls @{fg shine}ScanPartitions@{fg text} to publish the card's partitions into
    @{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} , then @{fg shine}MountPartitions@{fg text} to mount them. On removal it calls
    @{fg shine}MarkAbsent@{fg text} (keep the handler) or @{fg shine}UnmountPartitions@{fg text} (unmount and remove). This
    is what automounts FAT cards. In @{fg shine}compactflash.device@{fg text} automount is on by
    default; @{fg shine}AUTOMOUNT 0@{fg text} in @{fg shine}cfd.prefs@{fg text} turns it off. @{fg shine}ScanPartitions@{fg text} runs the same
    scanner the cold path uses (RDB, MBR, GPT, flat). Partitions already published
    (the cold-boot card, or a previous scan of the same card) are skipped one by
    one, so nothing is published twice.

One parser serves all three readers: the driver, the FAT handler, and
the lister all read the same published partition list.

----------------------------------------
@{"<< Prev" link ptable_library__unified_partition_table_library}  @{"Contents" link Main}  @{"Next >>" link Flows}

@endnode

@node Flows "Flows"
@{b}Flows@{ub}

The four use cases, shown as the LVO calls each one drives. They all end
at @{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} , the shared registry.

@{b}Cold-boot RDB autoboot.@{ub} The @{fg shine}compactflash.dosboot@{fg text} cold stub calls
@{fg shine}BootScanPartitions@{fg text} ; bootable RDB partitions become boot-menu entries,
the rest mountable volumes.

@{fg highlight}
  +---------------------------+                       
  |    compactflash.dosboot   |                       
  +---------------------------+                       
                |                                     
                |                                     
                |                                     
                |                                     
                v                                     
  +---------------------------+                       
  |     BootScanPartitions    |                       
  +---------------------------+                       
                |                                     
                |                                     
                |                                     
                |                                     
                v                                     
  +---------------------------+                       
  |scan RDB + load FS handlers|----mountable----+     
  +---------------------------+                 |     
                |                               |     
                |                               |     
            bootable                            |     
                |                               |     
                v                               v     
  +---------------------------+           +----------+
  |        AddBootNode        |           |AddDosNode|
  +---------------------------+           +----------+
                |                               |     
                |                               |     
                |                               |     
                |                               |     
                v                               |     
  +---------------------------+                 |     
  |     partition.resource    |<----------------+     
  +---------------------------+                       
@{fg text}

@{b}Hotplug attach (DOS time).@{ub} A card insert wakes the consumer's mount
worker, which publishes then mounts the card's partitions.

@{fg highlight}
  +--------------------+
  |    card insert     |
  +--------------------+
             |          
             |          
             |          
             |          
             v          
  +--------------------+
  |  mount-agent task  |
  +--------------------+
             |          
             |          
             |          
             |          
             v          
  +--------------------+
  |mount-worker process|
  +--------------------+
             |          
             |          
             |          
             |          
             v          
  +--------------------+
  |   ScanPartitions   |
  +--------------------+
             |          
             |          
             |          
             |          
             v          
  +--------------------+
  |  MountPartitions   |
  +--------------------+
             |          
             |          
             |          
             |          
             v          
  +--------------------+
  | partition.resource |
  +--------------------+
@{fg text}

@{b}Hotplug detach (card removed).@{ub} Two policies (see @{"Configuration" link configuration} ): keep the handler
(mark absent) or unmount and remove it.

@{fg highlight}
  +----------------------------+                                                          
  |        card remove         |                                                          
  +----------------------------+                                                          
                 |                                                                        
                 |                                                                        
                 |                                                                        
                 |                                                                        
                 v                                                                        
  +----------------------------+                                                          
  |    mount-worker process    |-------UNMOUNT-NONE-or-fs-not-listed--------+             
  +----------------------------+                                            |             
                 |                                                          |             
                 |                                                          |             
     default: all|supported fs                                              |             
                 |                                                          |             
                 v                                                          v             
  +----------------------------+                               +-------------------------+
  |UnmountPartitions prefixList|                               |        MarkAbsent       |
  +----------------------------+                               +-------------------------+
                 |                                                          |             
                 |                                                          |             
                 |                                                          |             
                 |                                                          |             
                 v                                                          v             
  +----------------------------+                               +-------------------------+
  |  entry unmounted, removed  |                               |entry kept, marked absent|
  +----------------------------+                               +-------------------------+
@{fg text}

@{b}Handler mount, auto-detect (e.g. fat95).@{ub} A handler probes a card, lets
@{fg shine}ScanPartitions@{fg text} publish the candidates, picks its partition, and overlays
its real DOS name with @{fg shine}RegisterPartition@{fg text} .

@{fg highlight}
  +---------------------------------------+
  |               mount MS:               |
  +---------------------------------------+
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      v                    
  +---------------------------------------+
  |             fat95 handler             |
  +---------------------------------------+
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      v                    
  +---------------------------------------+
  |             ScanPartitions            |
  +---------------------------------------+
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      v                    
  +---------------------------------------+
  |          select FAT partition         |
  +---------------------------------------+
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      v                    
  +---------------------------------------+
  |           RegisterPartition           |
  +---------------------------------------+
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      |                    
                      v                    
  +---------------------------------------+
  |partition.resource: real name + MOUNTED|
  +---------------------------------------+
@{fg text}

