@endnode

@node Public_interface__LVOs_ "Public interface (LVOs)"
@{b}Public interface (LVOs)@{ub}

For consumers. Full struct field layout for @{fg shine}MountCfg@{fg text} , @{fg shine}PartEntry@{fg text} , and
@{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} lives in the public header @{fg shine}../src/ptable_pub.i@{fg text}
(../src/ptable_pub.i).

@{fg highlight}
  BootScanPartitions(deviceName:a1, unit:d0)                 -30  cold-boot RDB scan + register
  ScanPartitions(deviceName:a1, unit:d0)                     -36  publish RDB/MBR/GPT/flat -> partition.resource
  MountPartitions(deviceName:a1, unit:d0, cfg:a0)            -42  AddDosNode(ADNF_STARTPROC) the entries
  UnmountPartitions(deviceName:a1, unit:d0, prefixList:a0)   -48  ACTION_DIE + RemDosEntry + free (prefixList=0: all; else by dostype, rest kept)
  RegisterPartition(deviceName:a1, unit:d0, ...)            -54  overlay a handler's real DOS name/flags onto an entry
  MarkAbsent(deviceName:a1, unit:d0)                         -60  card removed: clear PRESENT, keep handler in memory
@{fg text}

  * @{fg shine}OpenLibrary("ptable.library", 1)@{fg text} is enough for the cold-boot RDB path (
    @{fg shine}BootScanPartitions@{fg text} ); the DOS-time scan and mount calls require version @{fg shine}2@{fg text} . A
    v1 library has only @{fg shine}BootScanPartitions@{fg text} .
  * @{fg shine}BootScanPartitions@{fg text} runs from an @{fg shine}RTF_COLDSTART@{fg text} context (pre-DOS, single task).
    @{fg shine}RegisterPartition@{fg text} and @{fg shine}MarkAbsent@{fg text} are Exec-only; @{fg shine}MountPartitions@{fg text} and
    @{fg shine}UnmountPartitions@{fg text} must be called from a process.
  * @{fg shine}cfg@{fg text} is a @{fg shine}MountCfg@{fg text} (or @{fg shine}0@{fg text} for cold-boot defaults): global @{fg shine}mc_Flags@{fg text} and
    @{fg shine}mc_Control@{fg text} plus a 0-terminated per-dostype override table. The library
    resolves each entry by @{fg shine}(pe_DosType & $FFFFFF00)@{fg text} .
  * @{fg shine}ScanPartitions@{fg text} detects all four schemes; entries already published (by the
    cold path or a previous scan) are skipped one by one, so nothing publishes or
    mounts twice.
  * @{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} is the runtime single source of truth for discovered
    partitions; readers walk its list under @{fg shine}Forbid()@{fg text} or take its semaphore. Its
    layout and the @{fg shine}PartEntry@{fg text} fields are documented in @{fg shine}../src/ptable_pub.i@{fg text}
    (../src/ptable_pub.i).

----------------------------------------
@{"<< Prev" link What_it_looks_like__serial_debug_}  @{"Contents" link Main}  @{"Next >>" link See_also}

@endnode

@node See_also "See also"
@{b}See also@{ub}

  * @{"  __PAIRED_0__  " link "lsptres.guide/Main"} : the @{fg shine}lsptres@{fg text} CLI lists @{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} , every partition this library has
    published, its mount state, and the resolved Flags and CONTROL.
  * @{fg shine}cfd.prefs@{fg text} : the @{fg shine}FLAGS@{fg text} and @{fg shine}CONTROL@{fg text} keys (global and @{fg shine}_<fs>@{fg text} per filesystem) that
    @{fg shine}compactflash.device@{fg text} turns into the @{fg shine}MountCfg@{fg text} for @{fg shine}MountPartitions@{fg text} .
  * @{fg shine}compactflash.device@{fg text} (https://github.com/pulchart/cfd): the primary consumer
    (cold-boot autoboot + hotplug automount).
  * @{fg shine}fat95@{fg text} (https://github.com/pulchart/fat95): reads @{fg shine}partition.resource@{fg text} for
    whole-disk partition auto-detection.
  * @{fg shine}../src/ptable_pub.i@{fg text} (../src/ptable_pub.i): the public consumer header with
    full LVO, @{fg shine}MountCfg@{fg text} , and @{fg shine}PartEntry@{fg text} definitions.

----------------------------------------
@{"<< Prev" link Public_interface__LVOs_}  @{"Contents" link Main}

@endnode
